<span id="freeTextContainer6966321364943317929">Honestly, one of the best vampire novels I&apos;ve read in a long time. It&apos;s about time I read it to be honest. <br/><br/>Anne Rice does a great job at making us feel for even the proverbial &quot;bad guys&quot; in the book. I found myself enjoying the character of Armand the most. <br/><br/>Although, I didn&apos;t enjoy the awkward &quot;romantic&quot; scenes between Louis and vampire-child Claudia. <br/><br/></span>
  <span id="freeText6966321364943317929" style="display:none">Honestly, one of the best vampire novels I've read in a long time. It's about time I read it to be honest. <br /><br />Anne Rice does a great job at making us feel for even the proverbial "bad guys" in the book. I found myself enjoying the character of Armand the most. <br /><br />Although, I didn't enjoy the awkward "romantic" scenes between Louis and vampire-child Claudia. <br /><br /></span>
